DataElement.preferredName: Imaging Technique Observation Reuse Template Study Activity Repeat Frequency Ratio ISO21090.RTO.INT,PQ.TIME.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: An activity defined at the global library level whose intention is to obtain pictures of the interior or exterior of the body usually for diagnostic reasons. EXAMPLE(S): X-ray, MRI A ratio representing the number of occurrences of an activity within a given time period. EXAMPLE(S): Once per 12 hours; 2 times per day
